title: Hawaii Statewide GIS Program, Historic Land Divisions (Ahupua'a), Oahu Hawaii, 1996
name: Hawaii Statewide GIS Program, Historic Land Divisions (Ahupua'a), Oahu Hawaii, 1996
description:
Historical land division boundaries for the island of Oahu.
		Polygon coverage of O`ahu showing pre-Mahele (ca.1850)
                 ahupua`a boundaries, and coastlines ca. 1900.
		Commonly referred to as ahupuaa boundaries, but these boundaries
		changed and evolved over time, therefore, Historic Preservation Division 					
		refers to the layer as historic land divisions.
		
Source:		State Department of Land and Natural Resources, Historic 
		Preservation Division, 1996.
